<div class="bio-content">
    <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-secondary)] dark:text-[var(--color-secondary-dark)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I am a Founding Research Scientist at Poetiq, working on all things AI.
        Earlier, I was a Research Scientist at Google DeepMind, where I worked on Learned Compression and Generative Models.
        I received my PhD in Computer Science from University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, where I was advised by Prof. David Forsyth and Prof. Derek Hoiem.
        I received my MS from Robotics Institute, Carnegie Mellon University where I worked with Alyosha Efros, Abhinav Gupta and Martial Hebert.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-secondary)] dark:text-[var(--color-secondary-dark)]">
        I frequently serve as an area chair or reviewer at leading computer vision and ML conferences, including CVPR, ICCV, ECCV, ICLR and NeurIPS.
    </p>
</div>
